{
  "texts": [
    "Ho et al. (2023) present a hierarchical DL classification model, TaxonNet, to automate the taxonomic classification of carbonate skeletal grains from petrographic images, which can significantly aid in paleontological and sedimentary geological analysis.",
    "Taxon-Net adopts a multi-head architecture and can output multiple labels at numerous Linnaean taxonomic ranks for a single input image, mimicking the hierarchical nature of biologi- cal classification.",
    "This approach allows for a more nuanced and detailed classification of skeletal grains, which is particularly beneficial when dealing with datasets of limited size.",
    "The representation of three-dimensional skeletal grains in two-dimensional cross-sections is likely to affect the classification accuracy in this example.",
    "Liu and Song (2020) present fossil recognition from microfacies from thin-section images."
  ]
}